Heavy rain last night- level rose about .75" overnight.
Heavy rain last 2 days ~ 2".  Calm day-sunny.
Partial cloudy- but sunny @ time of test.
Bright sunny day- light wind- water level up approx. 8" due to snow melt + rain.
Partly cloudy but sun out when reading. slight wind making ripples + difficulty in getting accurate reading.
Slight wind but sunny. water had little algae.
Sunny- slight breeze- slight algae noticeable.
Partly cloudy.  Slight wind but okay for a good reading.  Water level: UP ABOUT 5 INCHES FROM LAST FALL.
Tree pollen on top near shoreline.  2.5 inches of rain 3 days ago.  Calm- partly cloudy day.
Slight breeze- sunny.  Tree pollen still noticeable in water.
Thin high cirrus clouds.  Very slight breeze.  2 to 3 inches of rain in the last 10 days.
Clear and calm- perfect for a test
Perfect day- no wind- bright sun.
High thin clouds but bright sun.
No rain in 2 weeks.  High thin clouds- but bright sun- slight breeze.
Clear and calm.  No rain in 4 weeks.
Clear and calm.  2" rain in last 2 months.
Bright sun but pollen.  Heavy on surface near shore- but clouded below surface with some kind of white colored specs ( ) making visibility poor from last check.
Bright with slight wind.  Light pollen- but still heavy under surface specs.
Bright sun.  Slight wind.  Hot last week.  Under surface still not clear.
Sunny- calm.  Still clouding (specs) under surface.  Don't know what the small specs are under surface- but it looks like small white granules of something like farina or cream of wheat similarity.
Bright sun- water seemed darker- and calm.
Clear- calm- and good checking weather.
First time doing test for these volunteers.  Sandy

column1: came out and demonstrated how- Thank you.
Heavy Storms on 7/21 and 7/22.  Southwest moderate wind.

column2: Sunny with light Southwest Wind.  Lake is calm.
First snow on 10/5 - snow on ground.  South wind is moderate.  As far as ice in and ice out our lake follows the same day/pattern as Lake Minocqua (at least for the past 13 years I've seen).
Windy- NE wind- warm a few days before- calm.  Ice out 4/17/03 - loons first landing: 4/24/03.
Overcast- partly sunny and windy - south.
Partly Sunny w/calm ripple-snow and frost-snow in
May:  Inclement weather - no testing.  Ice off lake 4/16/2004.  6/22/04:  Light south wind- partly sunny.  First loon arrived 4/23/2004.
Light SW wind.  Sunny.  Lake slight ripple- mostly calm.
Clear and cool.  Partly cloudy.  Light ripple.
Cloudy- light ripple.  S wind.  Took Secchi test on all 3 sides off boat.
Clear- blue sky.  Ice off lake 4/18/2005.  First loon 4/28/2005.
Windy but sunny.  So a slight ripple on the lake.
Partly cloudy skies. Temperature in high 70s/low 80s. This report was co-prepared by Larry Tenhaken.
overcast skies. water appearance was clear- green in color.
Skies -- clear; Lake level -- low; Water appearance -- clear; Water color -- green
Partly cloudy skies; water low- but higher than previous few years; water clear; green in color.
Sunny- cloudless skies; air temperature in high 70s - low 80s.
Sunny day; almost cloudless; temperature in mid- to high70s.

column1: Water temperature gauge was found to be broken on 8/29. Gauge was replaced and water temps were taken on Sept. 6.

column2: It was a windy day.  Tests could still be done but water temp probe was difficult to use today because boat kept drifting around anchor point.
There was a pretty stiff breeze today- but otherwise it was perfect.
sunny but breezy.  A bit difficult to keep boat from "spinning" and test equipment ending up under the boat.
